static.rb - A file loaded for all directories in the path
rstatic.rb - Like static, but recursive (for subdirectories)
*.rb - Files loaded when the page is accessed.

www/
  html/   --Default Web Root
  lib/    --Your libraries
    js/         --Javascript
    css/        --CSS
    sass/       --Sass CSS
    less/       --Less CSS
    plugins/    --Ruby Plugins (global)
    .libspec    --Defines what libs are loaded for what pages
  config.rb     --Config file. Declares VHosts among other things


-- NEW --

~/www/              -- Web Root Folder
  public/           -- Files the users see (Vhost :80, configurable)
  waitress/         -- Reserved for Waitress Configuration
    lib/            -- Libraries that can be used by pages
      js/           -- JavaScript libraries (auto-version e.g. jquery-v-e-r.min.js)
      css/          -- CSS Libraries
      sass/         -- SASS CSS
      less/         -- Less CSS
      ruby/         -- Ruby files/variables to load when parsing a webpage

REST Builder? e.g. doma.in/user/:userid/:data?scon

FILE FORMAT

*.rbhtml            -- Files served and interpreted by Waitress
  ```
    |-
    | JS = ["jquery", "mylib"]
    | CSS = ["styles", "compiled_less_or_sass"]
    | LOAD = ["variables"]
    |-
  ```
